<!-- SC_OFF --><div class="md"><p>I saw the Ben Stokes Film Trailer and couldn&#39;t help but think about other Cricketers who underwent similar comeback Stories who we don&#39;t really know/Talk about</p> <p>Case in Point: Lasith Malinga in the 2012 Finals was absolutely torn apart by Marlon Samuels and Darren Sammy (0-54 was one of the Top 3 Worst Bowling Performances ever at the time) and Simultaneously came back Stronger and evolved his bowling nature and Bamboozled Yuvraj Dhoni and Kohli who all had traditionally played him EXTREMELY well too finally win a Final after 4 Defeats in them.</p> <p>Also Jason Roy who couldn&#39;t pass 20 in 9 consecutive Innings and got Dropped for the Champions Trophy 2017 in Favour of Hales/Vince and Subsequently in the World Cup became one of the most Vital Cogs of the team.</p> <p>What others come to your mind?</p> </div><!-- SC_ON --> &#32; submitted by &#32; <a href="https://www.reddit.com/user/T_Lawliet"> /u/T_Lawliet </a> <br/> <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/Cricket/comments/wbwiqg/what_do_you_think_are_the_most_underrated/">[link]</a></span> &#32; <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/Cricket/comments/wbwiqg/what_do_you_think_are_the_most_underrated/">[comments]</a></span>